---
---

<section class="section patterns">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="patterns-header">
      <p class="eyebrow">Under the hood</p>
      <h2 class="h1">Not just AI. Real statistics.</h2>
      <p class="subhead">
        Most AI health apps read your data and guess. Meld runs actual statistical tests.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="patterns-grid">
      <div class="pattern-step card-glass reveal">
        <div class="step-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M21 12a9 9 0 1 1-9-9"/>
            <path d="M21 3v6h-6"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="h3">30 days of your data</h3>
        <p>
          Meld collects sleep, food, workouts, HR, HRV, and recovery
          from every source you connect. After 30 days it has enough
          signal to start looking for patterns.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pattern-step card-glass reveal">
        <div class="step-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M3 3v18h18"/>
            <path d="m7 12 4-4 4 4 4-4"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="h3">Test every pair</h3>
        <p>
          Protein vs deep sleep. Workout intensity vs next-day HRV.
          Dinner timing vs sleep onset. Meld tests correlations across
          every domain, not just the obvious ones.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pattern-step card-glass reveal">
        <div class="step-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/>
            <path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="h3">Control for false discovery</h3>
        <p>
          With dozens of metric pairs, some will look correlated by
          chance. Meld applies false-discovery correction so you only
          see patterns that hold up statistically, not lucky noise.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pattern-step card-glass reveal">
        <div class="step-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/>
            <polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/>
            <line x1="8" y1="13" x2="16" y2="13"/>
            <line x1="8" y1="17" x2="16" y2="17"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="h3">Validate against research</h3>
        <p>
          If a pattern survives statistical testing, Meld checks it
          against published studies. You see the finding AND the paper
          behind it. Not a hunch. Not a hallucination.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="patterns-bottom">
      413 automated tests verify this pipeline before every release.
      The coach only tells you what the numbers actually show.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .patterns {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-primary) 0%, var(--purple-50) 100%);
  }

  .patterns-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-12);
  }

  .patterns-header .h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
  }

  .patterns-header .subhead {
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .patterns-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--sp-5);
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  @media (min-width: 680px) {
    .patterns-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 1100px) {
    .patterns-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .pattern-step {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
  }

  .step-icon {
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    background: var(--purple-100);
    color: var(--purple-600);
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .pattern-step .h3 {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .pattern-step p {
    font-size: var(--fs-body-sm);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--lh-relaxed);
  }

  .patterns-bottom {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: var(--sp-10);
    font-size: var(--fs-body-sm);
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    font-weight: var(--fw-medium);
  }
</style>
